10/20/17, 11:18 - Nadeem Bhai: One of the beautiful names of our Rabb is - 

Al - Mu'min - The Bestower of Faith, Ima'an, tranquility.

We are human beings and we are no robots, we are blessed with intellect and we have emotions as well. 
We as individuals live in a society and the society we Iive in, affects our life. 
Sometimes, it happens that the circumstances around us, the trials, the fear, the alienation of being strange to the majority of wrong concepts around us, the downs of life take our hearts, (about which is said that there is a lump of flesh in body, if it is sound everything is sound and if it is corrupt then the whole body is corrupt and verily it is heart) deep down the depth where it seems there is nothing but envelopes of darkness and despair. 
But He swt, Al Mumin, The Bestower of Faith, Ima'an and tranquility bestows His Mercy, Yaqeen and despite all odds, one again rises from the ashes with the spirit to ignite others too and this is something which is bestowed by Him only, The Provider of tranquility. 
He swt through His unique ways inspire His slaves to have yaqeen in His promises, in the unseen, the life after death, the resurrection, the reckoning, the rewards, the punishments, the heaven and the hell to believe in all this and keep striving despite all the "apparent" failures. 

SubhanAllahi wabihamdihi SubhanAllahil Azeem.

‡§è‡§ï ‡§∏‡§™‡§®‡§æ ‡§•‡§æ ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§Ö‡§ß‡•Ç‡§∞‡§æ ‡§∞‡§π ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ó‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§•‡§æ ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§ó‡•Ç‡§Å‡§ó‡§æ ‡§π‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§è‡§ï ‡§≤‡•å ‡§•‡•Ä ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§Ö‡§®‡§®‡•ç‡§§ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§µ‡§ø‡§≤‡•Ä‡§® ‡§π‡•ã ‡§ó‡§à‡•§ ‡§∏‡§™‡§®‡§æ ‡§•‡§æ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ê‡§∏‡•á ‡§∏‡§Ç‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§≠‡§Ø ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§≠‡•Ç‡§ñ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§∞‡§π‡§ø‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã‡§ó‡§æ, ‡§ó‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§•‡§æ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ê‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§π‡§æ‡§ï‡§æ‡§µ‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ó‡•Ä‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ó‡•Ç‡§Å‡§ú ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§ó‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§¨ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ó‡§Ç‡§ß ‡§•‡•Ä‡•§ ‡§≤‡•å ‡§•‡•Ä ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ê‡§∏‡•á ‡§¶‡•Ä‡§™‡§ï ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§∞‡§æ‡§§ ‡§≠‡§∞ ‡§ú‡§≤‡§§‡§æ ‡§∞‡§π‡§æ, ‡§π‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡§Å‡§ß‡•á‡§∞‡•á ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≤‡§°‡§º‡§§‡§æ ‡§∞‡§π‡§æ ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§∞‡§æ‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ ‡§¶‡§ø‡§ñ‡§æ‡§ï‡§∞, ‡§è‡§ï ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§≠‡§æ‡§§ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§®‡§ø‡§∞‡•ç‡§µ‡§æ‡§£ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§™‡•ç‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§

‡§Æ‡•É‡§§‡•ç‡§Ø‡•Å ‡§ß‡•ç‡§∞‡•Å‡§µ ‡§π‡•à, ‡§∂‡§∞‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§®‡§∂‡•ç‡§µ‡§∞ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§ï‡§≤ ‡§ï‡§Ç‡§ö‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏ ‡§ï‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§π‡§Æ ‡§ö‡§Ç‡§¶‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ö‡§ø‡§§‡§æ ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§ö‡§¢‡§º‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§Ü‡§è, ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ ‡§®‡§æ‡§∂ ‡§®‡§ø‡§∂‡•ç‡§ö‡§ø‡§§ ‡§•‡§æ‡•§ ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§® ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§Ø‡§π ‡§ú‡§º‡§∞‡•Ç‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§•‡§æ ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§Æ‡•å‡§§ ‡§á‡§§‡§®‡•Ä ‡§ö‡•ã‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§õ‡§ø‡§™‡•á ‡§Ü‡§§‡•Ä? ‡§ú‡§¨ ‡§∏‡§Ç‡§ó‡•Ä-‡§∏‡§æ‡§•‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•ã‡§è ‡§™‡§°‡§º‡•á ‡§•‡•á, ‡§ú‡§¨ ‡§™‡§π‡§∞‡•á‡§¶‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§¨‡•á‡§ñ‡§¨‡§∞ ‡§•‡•á, ‡§π‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•á ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§µ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§è‡§ï ‡§Ö‡§Æ‡•Ç‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§®‡§ø‡§ß‡§ø ‡§≤‡•Å‡§ü ‡§ó‡§à‡•§ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§∞‡§§ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§∂‡•ã‡§ï‡§Æ‡§ó‡•ç‡§®‡§æ ‡§π‡•à ‚Äì ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ ‡§∏‡§¨‡§∏‡•á ‡§≤‡§æ‡§°‡§º‡§≤‡§æ ‡§∞‡§æ‡§ú‡§ï‡•Å‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ñ‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§®‡§µ‡§§‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§ñ‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§®‡§Æ‡§®‡§æ ‡§π‡•à ‚Äì ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ ‡§™‡•Å‡§ú‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§∂‡§æ‡§Ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§Ö‡§∂‡§æ‡§Ç‡§§ ‡§π‡•à ‚Äì ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ ‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§ï ‡§ö‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§¶‡§≤‡§ø‡§§‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§∏‡§π‡§æ‡§∞‡§æ ‡§õ‡•Ç‡§ü ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§ú‡§® ‡§ú‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§Ü‡§Å‡§ñ ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ü‡•Ç‡§ü ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§Ø‡§µ‡§®‡§ø‡§ï‡§æ ‡§™‡§æ‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§µ‡§ø‡§∂‡•ç‡§µ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∞‡§Ç‡§ó‡§Æ‡§Ç‡§ö ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§Æ‡•Å‡§ñ ‡§Ö‡§≠‡§ø‡§®‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡§æ ‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§§‡§ø‡§Æ ‡§Ö‡§≠‡§ø‡§®‡§Ø ‡§¶‡§ø‡§ñ‡§æ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡§∞‡•ç‡§ß‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§® ‡§π‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§

‡§Æ‡§π‡§∞‡•ç‡§∑‡§ø ‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡•ç‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§ï‡§ø ‡§®‡•á ‡§∞‡§æ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§£ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§≠‡§ó‡§µ‡§æ‡§® ‡§∞‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§Æ‡•ç‡§¨‡§Ç‡§ß ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ ‡§π‡•à ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§µ‡•á ‡§Ö‡§∏‡§Ç‡§≠‡§µ‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§®‡•ç‡§µ‡§Ø ‡§•‡•á‡•§ ‡§™‡§Ç‡§°‡§ø‡§§‡§ú‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§µ‡§® ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Æ‡§π‡§æ‡§ï‡§µ‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§â‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§•‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ù‡§≤‡§ï ‡§¶‡§ø‡§ñ‡§æ‡§à ‡§¶‡•á‡§§‡•Ä ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§µ‡§π ‡§∂‡§æ‡§Ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•Å‡§ú‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä, ‡§ï‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡•Å ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Ö‡§ó‡•ç‡§∞‡§¶‡•Ç‡§§ ‡§•‡•á; ‡§µ‡•á ‡§Ö‡§π‡§ø‡§Ç‡§∏‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§â‡§™‡§æ‡§∏‡§ï ‡§•‡•á, ‡§ï‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡•Å ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡§æ‡§ß‡•Ä‡§®‡§§‡§æ ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§π‡§∞ ‡§π‡§•‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≤‡§°‡§º‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§π‡§ø‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§§‡•Ä ‡§•‡•á‡•§

‡§µ‡§π ‡§∂‡§æ‡§Ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•Å‡§ú‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä, ‡§ï‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡•Å ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§æ‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Ö‡§ó‡•ç‡§∞‡§¶‡•Ç‡§§ ‡§•‡•á; ‡§µ‡•á ‡§Ö‡§π‡§ø‡§Ç‡§∏‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§â‡§™‡§æ‡§∏‡§ï ‡§•‡•á, ‡§ï‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡•Å ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡§æ‡§ß‡•Ä‡§®‡§§‡§æ ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§π‡§∞ ‡§π‡§•‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≤‡§°‡§º‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§π‡§ø‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§§‡•Ä ‡§•‡•á‡•§ 
‡§µ‡•á ‡§µ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§ï‡•ç‡§§‡§ø‡§ó‡§§ ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡§æ‡§ß‡•Ä‡§®‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§•‡§ï ‡§•‡•á ‡§ï‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡•Å ‡§Ü‡§∞‡•ç‡§•‡§ø‡§ï ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§æ‡§®‡§§‡§æ ‡§≤‡§æ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡§ø‡§¨‡§¶‡•ç‡§ß ‡§•‡•á‡•§ ‡§â‡§®‡•ç‡§π‡•ã‡§Ç‡§®‡•á ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡•å‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≠‡§Ø ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§ï‡§ø‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡•Å ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≠‡§Ø‡§≠‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡•å‡§§‡§æ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§™‡§æ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§® ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§ö‡•Ä‡§® ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡§ø ‡§â‡§®‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§®‡•Ä‡§§‡§ø ‡§á‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§Ö‡§¶‡•ç‡§≠‡•Å‡§§ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡•ç‡§Æ‡§ø‡§∂‡•ç‡§∞‡§£ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡•Ä‡§ï ‡§•‡•Ä‡•§ ‡§â‡§∏‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§â‡§¶‡§æ‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§•‡•Ä, ‡§¶‡•É‡§¢‡§º‡§§‡§æ ‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§•‡•Ä‡•§ ‡§Ø‡§π ‡§¶‡•Å‡§∞‡•ç‡§≠‡§æ‡§ó‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§π‡•à ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§á‡§∏ ‡§â‡§¶‡§æ‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¶‡•Å‡§∞‡•ç‡§¨‡§≤‡§§‡§æ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡§æ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§ú‡§¨‡§ï‡§ø ‡§ï‡•Å‡§õ ‡§≤‡•ã‡§ó‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§®‡•á ‡§â‡§®‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§¶‡•É‡§¢‡§º‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§π‡§†‡§µ‡§æ‡§¶‡§ø‡§§‡§æ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡§æ‡•§ 
‡§Æ‡•Å‡§ù‡•á ‡§Ø‡§æ‡§¶ ‡§π‡•à, ‡§ö‡•Ä‡§®‡•Ä ‡§Ü‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§Æ‡§£ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§¶‡§ø‡§®‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ú‡§¨ ‡§π‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•á ‡§™‡§∂‡•ç‡§ö‡§ø‡§Æ‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§§‡•ç‡§∞ ‡§á‡§∏ ‡§¨‡§æ‡§§ ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§Ø‡§§‡•ç‡§® ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§∞‡§π‡•á ‡§•‡•á ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§π‡§Æ ‡§ï‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§∂‡•ç‡§® ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§™‡§æ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§® ‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡•ã‡§à ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡•å‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§≤‡•á‡§Ç ‡§§‡§¨ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§¶‡§ø‡§® ‡§Æ‡•à‡§Ç‡§®‡•á ‡§â‡§®‡•ç‡§π‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¨‡§°‡§º‡§æ ‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡•Å‡§¶‡•ç‡§ß ‡§™‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ ‡§ú‡§¨ ‡§â‡§®‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§ï‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§∂‡•ç‡§® ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù‡•å‡§§‡§æ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§π‡•ã‡§ó‡§æ ‡§§‡•ã ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¶‡•ã ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§≤‡§°‡§º‡§®‡§æ ‡§™‡§°‡§º‡•á‡§ó‡§æ ‡§§‡•ã ‡§¨‡§ø‡§ó‡§°‡§º ‡§ó‡§è ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§π‡§®‡•á ‡§≤‡§ó‡•á ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§Ö‡§ó‡§∞ ‡§Ü‡§µ‡§∂‡•ç‡§Ø‡§ï‡§§‡§æ ‡§™‡§°‡§º‡•á‡§ó‡•Ä ‡§§‡•ã ‡§π‡§Æ ‡§¶‡•ã‡§®‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§∞‡•ç‡§ö‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§≤‡§°‡§º‡•á‡§Ç‡§ó‡•á‡•§ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§¶‡§¨‡§æ‡§µ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ü‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§µ‡•á ‡§¨‡§æ‡§§‡§ö‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ñ‡§ø‡§≤‡§æ‡§´ ‡§•‡•á‡•§

 ‡§Æ‡§π‡•ã‡§¶‡§Ø, 

‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏ ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡§§‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§µ‡•á ‡§∏‡•á‡§®‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§Ç‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§ï ‡§•‡•á, ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§µ‡§π ‡§∏‡•ç‡§µ‡§§‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡§æ ‡§∏‡§Ç‡§ï‡§ü‡§æ‡§™‡§®‡•ç‡§® ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡•ç‡§™‡•Ç‡§∞‡•ç‡§£ ‡§∂‡§ï‡•ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§æ‡§• ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•Ä ‡§π‡•ã‡§ó‡•Ä‡•§ ‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏ ‡§∞‡§æ‡§∑‡•ç‡§ü‡•ç‡§∞‡•Ä‡§Ø ‡§è‡§ï‡§§‡§æ ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡§ñ‡§Ç‡§°‡§§‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§µ‡•á ‡§â‡§®‡•ç‡§®‡§æ‡§Ø‡§ï ‡§•‡•á, ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§µ‡§π ‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§µ‡§ø‡§™‡§¶‡§ó‡•ç‡§∞‡§∏‡•ç‡§§ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§π‡§∞ ‡§Æ‡•Ç‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§ö‡•Å‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§â‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§Ø‡§Æ ‡§∞‡§ñ‡§®‡§æ ‡§π‡•ã‡§ó‡§æ‡•§ ‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§∞‡§§‡•Ä‡§Ø ‡§≤‡•ã‡§ï‡§§‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§â‡§®‡•ç‡§π‡•ã‡§Ç‡§®‡•á ‡§∏‡•ç‡§•‡§æ‡§™‡§®‡§æ ‡§ï‡•Ä, ‡§â‡§∏‡•á ‡§∏‡§´‡§≤ ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§Ü‡§ú ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡•á ‡§≠‡§µ‡§ø‡§∑‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§§‡§ø ‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§Ü‡§∂‡§Ç‡§ï‡§æ‡§è‡§Ç ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§ï‡§ü ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§æ ‡§∞‡§π‡•Ä ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç‡•§ ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•Ä ‡§è‡§ï‡§§‡§æ ‡§∏‡•á, ‡§Ö‡§®‡•Å‡§∂‡§æ‡§∏‡§® ‡§∏‡•á, ‡§Ü‡§§‡•ç‡§Æ-‡§µ‡§ø‡§∂‡•ç‡§µ‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§á‡§∏ ‡§≤‡•ã‡§ï‡§§‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§∏‡§´‡§≤ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§ï‡•á ‡§¶‡§ø‡§ñ‡§æ‡§®‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§®‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§ö‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§Ö‡§®‡•Å‡§Ø‡§æ‡§Ø‡•Ä ‡§∞‡§π ‡§ó‡§è‡•§ ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§∞‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§Ö‡§∏‡•ç‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§õ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§π‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ó ‡§¢‡•Ç‡§Å‡§¢‡§®‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§Ø‡§π ‡§è‡§ï ‡§Æ‡§π‡§æ‡§® ‡§™‡§∞‡•Ä‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§æ ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ï‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§Ø‡§¶‡§ø ‡§π‡§Æ ‡§∏‡§¨ ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§™‡§ø‡§§ ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§ï‡•á‡§Ç ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ê‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§π‡§æ‡§® ‡§â‡§¶‡•ç‡§¶‡•á‡§∂‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏‡§ï‡•á ‡§Ö‡§®‡•ç‡§§‡§∞‡•ç‡§ó‡§§ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§∞‡§§ ‡§∏‡§∂‡§ï‡•ç‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã, ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§• ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§Æ‡•É‡§¶‡•ç‡§ß ‡§π‡•ã ‡§î‡§∞ "‡§∏‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§π‡•Ç‡§Å ‡•§" ( ‡§Ö‡§∞‡§¨‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§∏‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∏‡•Ä  ‡§Ö‡§ï‡•ç‡§≤ ‡§ì ‡§§‡§¶‡§¨‡•ç‡§¨‡•Å‡§∞ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§∏‡§≤‡§æ ‡§π‡§≤ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡•á ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡•û‡§π‡§Æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ï‡§π‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡•§) 

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§∏‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§∏‡§§‡§¶‡§æ‡§®‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§≠‡§∞‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§•‡•Ä, ‡§â‡§∏‡•á ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§∏ "‡§ò‡•ã‡•ú‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Ö‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§¨‡§≤ ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§á‡§Ç‡§ö‡§æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ú" ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ ‡§≤‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ 
‡§ö‡§Ç‡§¶ ‡§¶‡§ø‡§®‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶ ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§®‡•á ‡§â‡§∏ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§∏‡§¨ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§π‡§Ç‡§ó‡•á ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡•õ‡•Ä‡•õ ‡§ò‡•ã‡•ú‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§§‡§æ‡§≤‡•ç‡§≤‡§ø‡•ò ‡§™‡•Ç‡§õ‡§æ, 
‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ, "‡§®‡§∏‡•ç‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä  ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡•§"

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§§‡§æ‡§ú‡•ç‡§ú‡•Å‡§¨ ‡§π‡•Å‡§Ü, ‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ú‡§Ç‡§ó‡§≤ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§∏‡§æ‡§à‡§∏ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¨‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§¶‡§∞‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§´‡•ç‡§§ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ..
‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§¨‡§§‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§ò‡•ã‡•ú‡§æ ‡§®‡§∏‡•ç‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç, ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§® ‡§á‡§∏‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡•à‡§¶‡§æ‡§Ø‡§∂ ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§á‡§∏‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç ‡§Æ‡§∞ ‡§ó‡§à ‡§•‡•Ä, ‡§Ø‡•á ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ó‡§æ‡§Ø ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§ß ‡§™‡•Ä ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§æ‡§• ‡§™‡§≤‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ 

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§®‡•á ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§Æ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§≤ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¨‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§™‡•Ç‡§õ‡§æ ‡§§‡•Å‡§Æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§™‡§§‡§æ ‡§ö‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ò‡•ã‡•ú‡§æ ‡§®‡§∏‡•ç‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ?" 
 
""‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ "‡§ú‡§¨ ‡§Ø‡•á ‡§ò‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à ‡§§‡•ã ‡§ó‡§æ‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§§‡§∞‡§π ‡§∏‡§∞ ‡§®‡•Ä‡§ö‡•á ‡§ï‡§∞‡§ï‡•á, ‡§ú‡§¨‡§ï‡§ø ‡§®‡§∏‡•ç‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§ò‡•ã‡•ú‡§æ ‡§ò‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§π ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§∏‡§∞ ‡§â‡§†‡§æ ‡§≤‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡•§"""üòä

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§´‡§∞‡§æ‡§∏‡§§ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§¨‡§π‡•Å‡§§ ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§§‡§æ‡§∏‡•ç‡§∏‡§ø‡§∞ ‡§π‡•Å‡§Ü, ‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§Æ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§≤ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ò‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡§®‡§æ‡§ú ,‡§ò‡•Ä, ‡§≠‡•Å‡§®‡•á ‡§¶‡•Å‡§Ç‡§¨‡•á, ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§™‡§∞‡§ø‡§Ç‡§¶‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§Ü‡§≤‡§æ ‡§ó‡•ã‡§∂‡•ç‡§§ ‡§¨‡§§‡•å‡§∞ ‡§á‡§®‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§≠‡§ø‡§ú‡§µ‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ 

‡§î‡§∞ ‡§â‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§≤‡§ø‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Æ‡§π‡§≤ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§§‡•à‡§®‡§æ‡§§ ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§¶‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ 
‡§ö‡§Ç‡§¶ ‡§¶‡§ø‡§®‡•ã ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶ , ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§®‡•á ‡§â‡§∏ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§¨‡•á‡§ó‡§Æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§¨‡§æ‡§∞‡•á ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§∞‡§æ‡§Ø ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç‡§ó‡•Ä, ‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ, "‡§§‡•å‡§∞ ‡§§‡§∞‡•Ä‡§ï‡•á ‡§§‡•ã ‡§Æ‡§≤‡§ø‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ú‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§® ‡§∂‡§π‡•õ‡§æ‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡•§"üòÇüòÇüòÇ

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•à‡§∞‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§§‡§≤‡•á ‡§ú‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§® ‡§®‡§ø‡§ï‡§≤ ‡§ó‡§à, ‡§π‡§µ‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§¶‡•Å‡§∞‡•Å‡§∏‡•ç‡§§ ‡§π‡•Å‡§è ‡§§‡•ã ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¨‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¨‡§§‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§∏‡§æ‡§∏ ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ "‡§π‡•ò‡•Ä‡•ò‡§§ ‡§Ø‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç,  ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§Ü‡§™‡§ï‡•á ‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡§ø‡§¶ ‡§®‡•á ‡§Æ‡•á‡§∞‡•á ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§µ‡§ø‡§Ç‡§¶ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§π‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§¨‡•á‡§ü‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡•à‡§¶‡§æ‡§Ø‡§∂ ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§∞‡§ø‡§∂‡•ç‡§§‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç‡§ó ‡§≤‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§•‡§æ, ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§® ‡§π‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§¨‡•á‡§ü‡•Ä 6 ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§π ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§∞ ‡§ó‡§à ‡§•‡•Ä, ‡§≤‡§ø‡§π‡§æ‡•õ‡§æ ‡§π‡§Æ ‡§®‡•á ‡§Ü‡§™‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π‡§§ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡§∞‡•Ä‡§¨‡•Ä ‡§§‡§æ‡§≤‡•ç‡§≤‡•Å‡•ò‡§æ‡§§ ‡•ò‡§æ‡§Ø‡§Æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§¨‡§ö‡•ç‡§ö‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•Ä ‡§¨‡•á‡§ü‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§®‡§æ ‡§≤‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§"

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§®‡•á ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§π‡§ø‡§¨ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§™‡•Ç‡§õ‡§æ "‡§§‡•Å‡§Æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§á‡§≤‡•ç‡§Æ ‡§π‡•Å‡§Ü ?"

""‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ, "‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§¶‡§ø‡§Æ‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∏‡§æ‡§• ‡§∏‡•Å‡§≤‡•Ç‡§ï ‡§ú‡§æ‡§π‡§ø‡§≤‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§¶‡§§‡§∞ ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡•§ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§®‡§¶‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä ‡§á‡§Ç‡§∏‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§¶‡•Ç‡§∏‡§∞‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§∏‡•á ‡§µ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§µ‡§π‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§π‡§ú‡§æ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§Ö‡§¶‡§¨ ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç, ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§∂‡§π‡§ú‡§æ‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¨‡§ø‡§≤‡•ç‡§ï‡•Å‡§≤ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡•§ """üòãüòãüòã

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§´‡§ø‡§∞ ‡§â‡§∏‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§´‡§∞‡§æ‡§∏‡§§ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§ñ‡•Å‡§∂ ‡§π‡•Å‡§Ü ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§¨‡§π‡•Å‡§§ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§Ö‡§®‡§æ‡§ú , ‡§≠‡•á‡•ú ‡§¨‡§ï‡§∞‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§Ç ‡§¨‡§§‡•å‡§∞ ‡§á‡§®‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§¶‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§∏‡§æ‡§• ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§â‡§∏‡•á ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§¶‡§∞‡§¨‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§Æ‡•á ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§§‡§Ø‡•ç‡§Ø‡§® ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§¶‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡•§ 

‡§ï‡•Å‡§õ ‡§µ‡§ï‡•ç‡§§ ‡§ó‡•Å‡•õ‡§∞‡§æ, ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§π‡§ø‡§¨ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¨‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ,‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§¨‡§æ‡§∞‡•á ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¶‡§∞‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§´‡•ç‡§§ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡•§

‡§Æ‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§π‡§ø‡§¨ ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ "‡§ú‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§Ö‡§Æ‡§æ‡§® ‡•§"ü§î

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§®‡•á ‡§µ‡§æ‡§¶‡§æ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡•§ 

‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ, "‡§® ‡§§‡•ã ‡§Ü‡§™ ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡•õ‡§æ‡§¶‡•á ‡§π‡•ã ‡§® ‡§Ü‡§™‡§ï‡§æ ‡§ö‡§≤‡§® ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§"

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§§‡§æ‡§µ ‡§Ü‡§Ø‡§æ, ‡§Æ‡§ó‡§∞ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§Ö‡§Æ‡§æ‡§® ‡§¶‡•á ‡§ö‡•Å‡§ï‡§æ ‡§•‡§æ, ‡§∏‡•Ä‡§ß‡§æ ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•Ä ‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡§ø‡§¶‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Æ‡§π‡§≤ ‡§™‡§π‡•Å‡§Ç‡§ö‡§æ ‡•§

‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤‡§ø‡§¶‡§æ ‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ, 
"‡§Ø‡•á ‡§∏‡§ö ‡§π‡•à, ‡§§‡•Å‡§Æ ‡§è‡§ï ‡§ö‡§∞‡§µ‡§æ‡§π‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§¨‡•á‡§ü‡•á ‡§π‡•ã, ‡§π‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§î‡§≤‡§æ‡§¶ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§•‡•Ä ‡§§‡•ã ‡§§‡•Å‡§Æ‡•ç‡§π‡•á ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§π‡§Æ ‡§®‡•á ‡§™‡§æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡•§"

‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§®‡•á ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§∏‡§æ‡§π‡§ø‡§¨ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§¨‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§™‡•Ç‡§õ‡§æ , ‡§¨‡§§‡§æ, "‡§§‡•Å‡§ù‡•á ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§á‡§≤‡•ç‡§Æ ‡§π‡•Å‡§Ü ????"

‡§â‡§∏‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§æ "‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡§ú‡§¨ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•ã "‡§á‡§®‡§æ‡§Æ ‡§ì ‡§á‡§ï‡§∞‡§æ‡§Æ" ‡§¶‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç, ‡§§‡•ã ‡§π‡•Ä‡§∞‡•á ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§§‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§µ‡§æ‡§π‡§∞‡§æ‡§§ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∂‡§ï‡•ç‡§≤ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§¶‡•á‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç....‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§® ‡§Ü‡§™ ‡§≠‡•á‡•ú, ‡§¨‡§ï‡§∞‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§Ç, ‡§ñ‡§æ‡§®‡•á ‡§™‡•Ä‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ö‡•Ä‡§ú‡•á‡§Ç ‡§á‡§®‡§æ‡§Ø‡§§ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç...‡§Ø‡•á ‡§Ö‡§∏‡§≤‡•Ç‡§¨ ‡§¨‡§æ‡§¶‡§∂‡§æ‡§π ‡•õ‡§æ‡§¶‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä,  ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§ö‡§∞‡§µ‡§æ‡§π‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§¨‡•á‡§ü‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§π‡•ã ‡§∏‡§ï‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§" üòÇüòÇüòÇ

2/24/18, 22:11 - Nadeem Bhai: *Cicero of the Roman empire wrote this about the situation during his lifetime:*

1. The poor - work & work.
2. The rich - exploit the poor.
3. The soldier - protects both.
4. The taxpayer - pays for all three.
5. The wanderer - rests for all four.
6. The drunk - drinks for all five.
7. The banker - robs all six.
8. The lawyer - misleads all seven.
9. The doctor - bills all eight.
10. The undertaker - buries all nine.
11. The Politician - lives happily on account of all ten.

*Written in 43 B.C., but valid even today.*

1. You wear a abaya and hijab but with perfume and makeup. (a leaking bucket)

2. You are following the Sunnah and have a beard but you don‚Äôt lower your gaze. (a leaking bucket)

3. You pray all of your prayers on time but you have no Khushu at all. (a leaking bucket)

4. You are very kind to people and speak with them gently, but with your family you are always harsh.  (a leaking bucket)

5. You honour and treat your guests well but when they leave, you gossip about them and talk about their flaws. ((a leaking bucket)

6. You give a lot of sadaqah to the poor but you humiliate and hurt them. (a leaking bucket)

7. You stand up for tahajjud at night, fast, pray and read Quran everyday but cut your family ties. (a leaking bucket)

8. You fast and have sabr for the pangs of hunger and thirst but you swear, insult and curse. (a leaking bucket)

9. You help others but you are doing it to gain something from them and not doing this act of kindness for the sake of Allah‚Äôs Glory. (a leaking bucket)

10. You post reminders and have thousands of followers on Facebook and social media but you are doing it for the fame, not to please Allah. (a leaking bucket)

5/26/18, 04:42 - Nadeem Bhai: Let‚Äôs start with some Hellmatics.
According to hadith, if a stone is dropped from the top of Hell, it would take seventy years for the stone to reach the bottom. And of course we know it will melt from the intense heat before it even gets there.
That bottom, according to¬†Surah 4:145, belongs to the hypocrites. Not the mass murderers, not the adulterers, not the usurpers, not the tyrants, but the hypocrites.
What does the Prophet (SAW) say about hypocrisy?
Abdullah bin Amr (RA) narrated that Rasulillah (SAW) said,¬†‚ÄúWhoever has the following four characteristics will be a pure hypocrite and whoever has any one of the following characteristics will have the characteristics of a hypocrite:¬†¬†
1. Whenever he speaks, he lies,
2. Whenever he makes a covenant, he always shows treachery,¬†
3. Whenever he makes a promise, he breaks it.
4. Whenever he quarrels, he behaves in a very evil and insulting manner.‚Äù¬†[Sahih Bukhari: Book of Faith, Hadith 34]

You probably feel guilty now because you fear you bear the signs of hypocrisy. I won‚Äôt tell you to relax, but Umar ibn Al-Khattab (RA) also panicked for fear of being a hypocrite. The same Umar of whom the prophet said,¬†‚ÄúAmong the nations who came before you there were Muhaddathun (men who were inspired) and if there are any such men among my ummah, then ‚ÄòUmar ibn al-Khattaab is one of them.‚Äù¬†[Sahih Muslim: 2398]

On the fear of hypocrisy, a classical scholar, Ibn Al-Qayyim said, ‚ÄúThe more faith and knowledge a person has, the more he will fear that he may be among this class of people (hypocrites)‚Äù.
Hasan Al-Basri even added that, ‚Äúno one feels safe from it (hypocrisy), except a hypocrite.‚Äù

These days, people throw around ‚Äòhypocrite‚Äô like it‚Äôs a complement.
It‚Äôs amazing some people have telepathic powers that they can tell who is a hypocrite and who isn‚Äôt. Might be experience, might be ignorance, Allah knows best.

Some understand hypocrisy to mean a person who sins in secret then speaks against the same sin in public, forgetting, or totally ignoring the words of Abubakr (RA) who used to say;
‚ÄúO Allah, You know me better than I know myself, and I know myself better than these people who praise me. Make me better than what they think of me, and forgive those sins of mine of which they have no knowledge, and do not hold me responsible for what they say.‚Äù
This doesn‚Äôt make the sins we do in secret right. May Allah forgive us.

Some, in the bid to prove they aren‚Äôt hypocrites, gladly show off the sins they commit in private, forgetting the words of the prophet when he said,¬†‚ÄúAll of my ummah will be forgiven except those who sin openly. It is a part of sinning openly when a man does something at night, then the following morning when Allah has concealed his sin, he says, ‚ÄòO So and so, I did such and such last night,‚Äô when all night his Lord has concealed him and the next morning he uncovers what Allah had concealed.‚Äù¬†(Al-Bukhari, 5721; Muslim, 2990).
So shame of exposing sins is a good sign after all. Still doesn‚Äôt mean Allah doesn‚Äôt see them.
When a person loses the sense of shame, he loses everything.


May Allah forgive our sins, conceal our secrets, and save us from hypocrisy.

The mistakes are mine and Allah knows best.

Ramadhaan Day 9 : Between Shame and Hypocrisy

9/11/18, 13:27 - Nadeem Bhai: Explain to your children how Taqwa is the major part of our religion and how to instil in our lives.

*What is Taqwa?* 

*Taqwa* is not only about manners..
 *Taqwa* is not about looking Islamic... 
 *Taqwa* is not about sporting a beard or wearing a Hijab...
 *Taqwa* is not about appearance

*BUT*

 *Taqwa* is when you miss a prayer, you feel uneasy the whole day...
 *Taqwa* is when you speak a lie, you feel bad...
 *Taqwa* is the guilt that follows when you hurt someone knowingly or unknowingly...
*Taqwa* is the shame and regret that follows a sin you committed knowing full well how it stands in the sight of Allah...
 *Taqwa* is when you cannot sleep after disobeying or disrespecting your parents...
 *Taqwa* is to cry in the depths of night fearing none but the one above the Arsh...
 *Taqwa* is the fear that refrains us from sinning when nobody familiar is around...
 *Taqwa* is the guts and the will to please Allah, even when the whole world is hell bent on displeasing Him...
 *Taqwa* is to wear that beard and Hijab for the sole reason of pleasing our Creator and to keep it on as per Sunnah....
 *Taqwa* is to stay happy and smiling, knowing that this world is a prison for believers...
 *Taqwa* is the good manners and character we practice for the sake of Allah...
 *Taqwa* is the struggle to better ourselves according to Islam, with each passing day...
 *Taqwa* is not just about rising in deen,   but about falling, rising again and never letting go!
 *Taqwa* is all about what is IN OUR HEARTS. 

 _And if our hearts are filled with proper *Taqwa*, then actions automatically follow..._
_And the sweetness of these actions is so fulfilling!_

 You are not forced to share....
 _*But as Allah Subhanahu Taala  says:*_ 
 _*Remind, for reminder benefits the believers*_ ‚ú®

‡§ó‡•Å‡§ú‡§∞‡§æ‡§§ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§®‡§§‡§æ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§≠‡§Ø‡§æ‡§®‡§ï ‡§Ü‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡•ã‡§∂ ‡§µ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§™‡•ç‡§§ ‡§•‡§æ‡•§ ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§ñ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§Æ‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§•‡•á- ‡§®‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç‡§¶‡•ç‡§∞ ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§¶‡•Ä‡•§ *‡§∏‡§æ‡§≤ 2019‡•§* ‡§¶‡•á‡§∂ ‡§≤‡•ã‡§ï‡§∏‡§≠‡§æ ‡§ö‡•Å‡§®‡§æ‡§µ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§π‡§æ‡§®‡•á ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§ñ‡•ú‡§æ ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ *‡§¶‡•á‡§∂ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§®‡§§‡§æ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§®‡•ã‡§ü‡§¨‡§Ç‡§¶‡•Ä, ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§è‡§∏‡§ü‡•Ä, ‡§∞‡§æ‡§´‡•á‡§≤ ‡§ò‡•ã‡§ü‡§æ‡§≤‡§æ, ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡§æ‡§® ‡§Ü‡§§‡•ç‡§Æ‡§π‡§§‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§ì‡§Ç, ‡§¨‡•ù‡§§‡•Ä ‡§¨‡•á‡§∞‡•ã‡§ú‡§ó‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä, ‡§¶‡§≤‡§ø‡§§ ‡§â‡§§‡•ç‡§™‡•Ä‡•ú‡§® ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§¶‡•á‡§∂, ‡§õ‡§§‡•ç‡§§‡•Ä‡§∏‡§ó‡•ù, ‡§ï‡§∞‡•ç‡§®‡§æ‡§ü‡§ï‡§æ, ‡§™‡§Ç‡§ú‡§æ‡§¨ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§∞‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ó‡§Ç‡§µ‡§æ* ‡§ö‡•Å‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§π‡•ã‡§§‡•Ä ‡§π‡•à‡•§
*‡§Ö‡§ö‡§æ‡§®‡§ï* ‡§è‡§ï ‡§¶‡•ã‡§™‡§π‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•á *‡§™‡•Å‡§≤‡§µ‡§æ‡§Æ‡§æ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§∏‡•Ä‡§Ü‡§∞‡§™‡•Ä‡§è‡§´ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§´‡§ø‡§≤‡•á ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§π‡§Æ‡§≤‡•á ‡§î‡§∞ 45 ‡§ú‡§µ‡§æ‡§®‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§∂‡§π‡§æ‡§¶‡§§* ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ñ‡§¨‡§∞ ‡§Ü‡§§‡•Ä ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§¶‡•á‡§∂ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞‡•á *‡§Æ‡•Å‡§¶‡•ç‡§¶‡•á ‡§≠‡•Å‡§≤‡§æ‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§¶‡•á‡§∂‡§≠‡§ï‡•ç‡§§‡§ø ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§≠‡§ü‡•ç‡§ü‡•Ä* ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§ù‡•ã‡§Ç‡§ï ‡§¶‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§Ø‡§π‡§æ‡§Å *‡§¶‡•ã ‡§§‡§•‡•ç‡§Ø* ‡§â‡§≤‡•ç‡§≤‡•á‡§ñ‡§®‡•Ä‡§Ø ‡§π‡•à-
*‡§™‡§π‡§≤‡§æ, ‡§¶‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§ø‡§£ ‡§∏‡§ø‡§®‡•á‡§Æ‡§æ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§µ‡§ø‡§ñ‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§§ ‡§Ö‡§≠‡§ø‡§®‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§™‡§µ‡§® ‡§ï‡§≤‡•ç‡§Ø‡§æ‡§£* ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§¨‡§Ø‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡§ø, "‡§≠‡§æ‡§ú‡§™‡§æ ‡§®‡•á‡§§‡§æ ‡§®‡•á ‡§¶‡•ã ‡§∏‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§™‡§π‡§≤‡•á ‡§π‡•Ä ‡§≤‡•ã‡§ï‡§∏‡§≠‡§æ ‡§ö‡•Å‡§®‡§æ‡§µ ‡§∏‡•á ‡§™‡§π‡§≤‡•á ‡§á‡§∏ ‡§§‡§∞‡§π ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§π‡§Æ‡§≤‡§æ ‡§π‡•ã‡§®‡•á ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§∞‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ö‡•Å‡§®‡§æ‡§µ ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§§‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§æ‡§§ ‡§ï‡§π‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§ó‡§†‡§¨‡§Ç‡§ß‡§® ‡§ï‡§æ ‡§™‡•ç‡§∞‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§µ ‡§∞‡§ñ‡§æ ‡§•‡§æ‡•§"
*‡§¶‡•Ç‡§∏‡§∞‡§æ, ‡§π‡§Æ‡§≤‡•á ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§∂‡§æ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§≤ '‡§Ö‡§≤‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡•û ‡§Ö‡§π‡§Æ‡§¶ ‡§∞‡§æ‡§•‡§∞',* ‡§ú‡§ø‡§∏‡§ï‡•ã ‡§è‡§ï ‡§Æ‡•Å‡§†‡§≠‡•á‡•ú ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç 9 ‡§Ö‡§ï‡•ç‡§ü‡•Ç‡§¨‡§∞ 2017 ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ó‡§ø‡§∞‡§´‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ ‡§ú‡§æ‡§§‡§æ ‡§π‡•à ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§¨‡§ø‡§®‡§æ ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§æ‡§Ç‡§ö ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡§ï‡•á ‡§Ü‡§¶‡•á‡§∂ ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§õ‡•ã‡•ú‡§æ ‡§ó‡§Ø‡§æ- ‡§Ø‡§π ‡§Ö‡§¨ ‡§§‡§ï ‡§Ö‡§®‡§∏‡•Å‡§≤‡§ù‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§

*‡§ï‡•Å‡§õ ‡§∏‡§µ‡§æ‡§≤* ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç, ‡§ú‡•ã ‡§á‡§∏ ‡§§‡§•‡•ç‡§Ø ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§§‡§∞‡§´ ‡§á‡§∂‡§æ‡§∞‡§æ ‡§ï‡§∞‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§ï‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç *‡§ö‡•Å‡§®‡§æ‡§µ‡•Ä ‡§≤‡§æ‡§≠ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§≤‡§ø‡§è ‡§π‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•á ‡§∏‡•à‡§®‡§ø‡§ï‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ú‡•Ä‡§µ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§¨‡§≤‡§ø* ‡§§‡•ã ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§ö‡•ù‡§æ‡§à ‡§ó‡§Ø‡•Ä-

1. *CRPF ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ú‡§µ‡§æ‡§®‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§π‡§µ‡§æ‡§à ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§ó ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç‡§ó ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§†‡•Å‡§ï‡§∞‡§æ‡§à?*

2. *CRPF ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§´‡§ø‡§≤‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§∞‡§æ‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡•á ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ú‡§æ‡§®‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§Ü‡§§‡§Ç‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§Æ‡§ø‡§≤‡•Ä?*

3. *350 ‡§ï‡§ø‡§≤‡•ã ‡§µ‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§´‡•ã‡§ü‡§ï ‡§™‡•Å‡§≤‡§ø‡§∏ ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§®‡§ú‡§∞‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§∏‡•á ‡§ï‡•à‡§∏‡•á ‡§¨‡§ö‡§æ?*

4. *‡§∏‡•Å‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§æ ‡§è‡§ú‡•á‡§Ç‡§∏‡§ø‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§®‡•á ‡§π‡§Æ‡§≤‡•á ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§™‡•Ç‡§∞‡•ç‡§µ ‡§∏‡•Ç‡§ö‡§®‡§æ ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡§ï‡•á ‡§ï‡§π‡§®‡•á ‡§™‡§∞ ‡§®‡§ú‡§∞‡§Ö‡§Ç‡§¶‡§æ‡§ú ‡§ï‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ?*


*‡§Æ‡§π‡§§‡•ç‡§µ‡§™‡•Ç‡§∞‡•ç‡§£ ‡§¨‡§æ‡§§- ‡§ú‡§Æ‡•ç‡§Æ‡•Ç&‡§ï‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡•Ä‡§∞ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§∞‡§æ‡§∑‡•ç‡§ü‡•ç‡§∞‡§™‡§§‡§ø ‡§∂‡§æ‡§∏‡§® ‡§ï‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞‡§£ ‡§∏‡§æ‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§∂‡§ï‡•ç‡§§‡§ø‡§Ø‡§æ‡§Ç ‡§Æ‡•ã‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§∏‡§∞‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞ ‡§ï‡•á ‡§π‡§æ‡§• ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§π‡•à‡•§*

‡§Ö‡§¨ ‡§Ü‡§™ ‡§Ü‡§∏‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä ‡§∏‡•á ‡§∏‡§Æ‡§ù ‡§∏‡§ï‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç ‡§ï‡§ø ‡§™‡•Å‡§≤‡§µ‡§æ‡§Æ‡§æ ‡§π‡§Æ‡§≤‡•á ‡§∏‡•á ‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§∞ ‡§µ‡§ø‡§Ç‡§ó ‡§ï‡§Æ‡§æ‡§Ç‡§°‡§∞ ‡§Ö‡§≠‡§ø‡§®‡§Ç‡§¶‡§® ‡§ï‡•á ‡§™‡§æ‡§ï‡§ø‡§∏‡•ç‡§§‡§æ‡§® ‡§ï‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•à‡§¶ ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§π‡•ã‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡•á ‡§¨‡§æ‡§µ‡§ú‡•Ç‡§¶ ‡§≠‡•Ä *‡§Æ‡•ã‡§¶‡•Ä ‡§î‡§∞ ‡§≠‡§æ‡§ú‡§™‡§æ ‡§®‡•á ‡§Ö‡§™‡§®‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§∞‡•ç‡§Ø‡§ï‡•ç‡§∞‡§Æ ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§∞‡§¶‡•ç‡§¶ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç* ‡§ï‡§ø‡§è? *‡§∞‡§ï‡•ç‡§∑‡§æ ‡§Æ‡§Ç‡§§‡•ç‡§∞‡•Ä ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§≤‡§æ‡§™‡§§‡§æ* ‡§π‡•Å‡§à? *‡§Ö‡§ú‡§ø‡§§ ‡§°‡•ã‡§≠‡§æ‡§≤ ‡§ï‡•ç‡§Ø‡•ã‡§Ç ‡§ö‡•Å‡§™* ‡§∞‡§π‡§æ?

*‡§≤‡•á‡§ï‡§ø‡§®, ‡§Ü‡§™‡§ï‡•ã ‡§ö‡•Å‡§™ ‡§®‡§π‡•Ä‡§Ç ‡§∞‡§π‡§®‡§æ ‡§π‡•à‡•§ ‡§Ü‡§™ ‡§ö‡•Å‡§™ ‡§∞‡§π‡•á ‡§§‡•ã ‡§Ö‡§ó‡§≤‡•á ‡§ï‡§æ‡§´‡§ø‡§≤‡•á ‡§Æ‡•á‡§Ç ‡§Ü‡§™‡§ï‡§æ ‡§¨‡•á‡§ü‡§æ, ‡§≠‡§æ‡§à, ‡§™‡§§‡§ø, ‡§™‡§ø‡§§‡§æ ‡§≠‡•Ä ‡§π‡•ã ‡§∏‡§ï‡§§‡•á ‡§π‡•à‡§Ç‡•§*

6/19/19, 13:41 - Saeed Bhai: We should make continuous investment in fundamental sciences and we should play a pioneering role in this regard. In other words, we should rush towards undiscovered truths in the world. There are many truths in the universe which have not been discovered yet, as was the case a 100 years ago when many of the findings that exist today had not been discovered yet. They existed in nature, but they had not been discovered.

It is not the case that electricity, for example, has just come into being. Since the creation of the world, it was there. Later on, some people showed determination, acted in an intelligent way and discovered it. We should be after finding the truths that have not been discovered yet. This is one of our fundamental tasks. Attending to fundamental sciences helps draw the scientific society towards the undiscovered truths in the universe. We should not merely work on the truths that have already been discovered and the moves that others have made in this area.

Imam Sayyed Ali Khamenei , May 29

9/14/19, 14:08 - Nadeem Bhai: Copied from a friend.............I've been trying to avoid Tabrez Ansari since yesterday. But his ghost, standing silently, bleeding on my carpet, refuses to leave. (And just after I got the carpet cleaned). So i write his story hoping it will get rid of him finally.

24 yr old Tabrez, married for three months, comes home to celebrate Eid with his family.  His first Eid as a husband; and his bride had some special news for him.

In his hometown he was caught by a mob which accused him of stealing a motorbike, tied him to a pole, beat him  with sticks and rods for hours and made him chant Jai Shri Ram and Jai Hanuman till he's nearly dead. The mob made videos of him, uploaded them on social media where they went viral.

The police finally arrive after hours and promptly arrested Tabrez, keeping him in custody despite critical injuries and finally take him to a hospital...where he dies. And his new bride loses her unborn baby with shock. Finally the police announce that there is no murder charge against the accused because Tabrez died in a hospital due to a cardiac arrest.

Since then Tabrez's ghost has been standing in my home, curious to know who killed him? 

I patiently explain to him.

 "Look Tabrez, what really killed you was your anti Hindu ways. You want to be an equal in a Hindu majority country. Does that make sense? Don't u know hum Hindu khatrey mein Hain? Have some pity for us poor victims.

Also did you realise your co-religionists carried out Islamic invasions a thousand years back and it's only just, that you should pay the price.

So chill with your destiny. Why can't you see how lucky you were to be born in the most tolerant country in the world?

Now buzz off and let me get back to writing my jokes. I did put a weepy emoji on your news you know!! What else do u want me to do?"

Understanding the strength of my logic, ghost Tabrez vanished. 
And I woke up with a gasp, thanking my stars that it was just a dream.

Then I saw Junaid, Akhlaq, Pehlu, Rakhbar,Asifa standing on my carpet.....

1/30/20, 12:48 - Nadeem Bhai: Sanjeev Kumar 12 questions about CAA and NRC  

1. Government and BJP is giving versions that the CAA and NRC are not linked. Has Amit Shah in his numerous speeches and  twits not himself claimed that the two are linked https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/lok-sabha-elections-2019-amit-shah-says-mamata-banerjee-extending-support-to-those-who-wish-to-divid-2031385 for desired results? Desired results could be interpreted as persecuting Muslims in the name of CAA and NRC, if both applied together? 

2. Is not the ruling dispensation spreading rumours that people are misguided and protesters are against giving citizenship to persecuted minorities. Is their a single proof about this? Has a single organisation demanded not giving citizenship to the persecuted minorities? People are only asking to make CAA religion neutral as per the basic character of the Indian Constitution? 

3. People want to know the basis of selecting Pakistan, Afghanistan and Bangladeshi? And why not China, Sri Lanka, Nepal and Myanmar, which share border with India? And minorities included in CAA are much more persecuted in these countries? People say when Hindus are persecuted where will they go if not India, whereas persecuted Muslims may have other countries too. But then Christians and Buddhists also have many countries to choose? In fact christian countries are very liberal in giving citizenship then why Christians included? 

4. CAA includes persecuted Buddhist, Hindus, Christians and Sikhs but leaves Jews and Muslims, where as certain sects of Muslims are more persecuted in Pakistan and liberal Muslims in Afghanistan than Hindus or Sikhs? If polarisation and political dividends is not the real agenda, then why not include Sri Lanka where Hindus have been persecuted more than anywhere else in the world. Their population has dropped from 18.5% in 1961 to 8% now. Why not include China where Buddhists have been hugely persecuted or Nepal where Christians persecuted. See details on google. Then why these three countries? Unless the agenda is to agitate Hindus by selecting only Muslim countries and hype persecution stories using fake data and false stories, which is currently flooding social media? 

5. Is not the Government abating the violence itself by making excessive use of force and police seen clearly in videos engaging in arson? The members of RSS infiltrating among the crowds in skull caps, as reported in Seelampur, Lucknow and in Murshidabad, where four RSS members have been arrested. Many RSS members were seen hurling provocative abuses on Jamia Milia students at protest sites, while police provided them cover?  Videos emerging police midnight crack down teams joined by plain cloth people who chant provocative slogans while ransacking houses? Who are these police Mitras in UP who are seen with police abating violence in UP? 

6. Did Government not have the powers under existing laws to give citizenships to migrants? In article in ET on 21 Dec, Union I&B Minister Mr Javadekar himself  claimed having given citizenship to millions after partition, then why this law? In 2019 itself Government gave citizenship to 745 minorities from Pakistan? As per media reports there are estimated 30,000 minorities from Pakistan stying in India. They could easily be given citizenship on one fine morning then why CAA?

7. What is the source of 23% minorities being reduced to 3% in Pakistan and 30% to 9% in Bangladesh, as claimed by the Home Minister while debating CAA in the Parliament. Is this not a total fake figures quoted when census figures of united Pakistan in 1951 showed combined population of minorities as 14.2% and that in west Pakistan as 3.4%, which has now increased to 3.7%, as per census figures quoted by India Today report? 

8. If an Army officer, Mr Sana Ullah who served Indian Army for 30 years and fought war in Cargill and was decorated by President Medal fails to prove his citizenship and is sent to detention camp, who else will be able to prove? Did he not have any certificates or was he a Bangladeshi serving Indian Army? What about much publicised Dinesh and his wife Tara Prajapathi who migrated to Assam from Eastern UP few decades back and could not produce documents and were sent to detention centre. Now under CAA they will get relief. What would be the fate of a Muslim family under similar situation? 

9. Did PM not misled the nation, knowingly or unknowingly, when he said at a election rally in Delhi a month back when he said there are no detention camps while his own Government sanctioned 45 crores for a detention camp in Assam last year and many more reported from different parts. Did PM not repeatedly claimed that NRC has never been discussed in his Government whereas the same finds mention in the President‚Äôs Address to the House and repeatedly asserted by HM? 

10. When both Hindus and Muslims illegally migrated into India, what is the basis to distinguish that Muslims came for better prospects and all Hindus came only due to persecution? Why would Hindus not come to India for better prospects when Muslims would come. Were all Hindus so well placed or so well treated there in Bangladesh that none would have come here for better prospects? Then how would Government establish and differentiate between work seeking Hindus and persecuted Hindus?

11. Once NRC is nationally rolled out, both Hindus and Muslims especially poor, labourers and landless will face tremendous amount of harassment and corruption in furnishing documents, as the Assam experience shows. At the end, in a village if 20 Hindus and 20 Muslims fail to pass NRC test, will both meet the same fate or Hindus will get citizenship invoking CAA and Muslims will get differentiated based on their religion and if so by what dictionary on this planet is CAA not brazenly communal? 

12. If the Government‚Äôs declared objective is to give citizenships to the persecuted minorities then will the CAA be withdrawn after giving citizenships to all the identified persecuted minorities in a definite period and thereafter  NRC will be implemented? If any persecuted minorities still left out, they may be given citizenship under the existing rules and provisions.
The real intention about bringing CAA be clear by the answer of the Government to the point number 12.

3/17/20, 18:28 - Dr. Jaun: Lets all be alert as we will enter stage 3 soon which is an outbreak of infection in community (from individual cases)....
Corona Virus precautions for house-holds:

1. Wash milk bags the moment we take it & wash your hands while you are at it.

2. Consider cancelling newspapers.

3. Keep a separate tray for couriers. Courier person can place the envelope/pkg in the tray and courier may be left untouched for at least 24 hours. 

4. Instruct maids not to touch main door. On entering the home, she has to immediatly wash hands thoroughly, before touching other things . After that, wipe the calling-bell switch with a cleaning fluid :)

3. Avoid getting swiggy, amazon etc as far as possible.

4. Wash all fruits and vegitables once we bring them home.

5. Remote, phone and keyboards are the most highly contaminated elements in our house. Clean them at least once a day using cleaning fluid.

6. Wash hands frequently when in house or in office. Once every hour at least.

7. Avoid public transport as far as possible. Even Ola and Uber may be used when absolutely unavoidable.

8. Avoid gyms, swimming pool and other exercise areas, where surface contact or air-borne contamination is inevitable.

9. Cancel tuitions, dance/music classes, etc.

10. When you return home from office, shopping, etc. discard your clothes and wash your hands and feet thoroughly.

11. Most importantly do not touch hands anywhere on face. Inform children and parents.

12. Ask senior citizens to stop going for the routine walking exercise. 

Please protect yourself and your loved ones. üôèüèª

4/5/20, 19:49 - Nadeem Bhai: *An OPEN LETTER To Narendra Modi by _Mr Khroku Nuh_, Dimapur*

Dear Mr. Namo,
Let us brace ourselves with some hard facts before jumping into your superstitious numerological belief with the number ‚Äô9‚Äô and the ‚Äòmoon‚Äô and the ‚Äòcosmos‚Äô.
India, as of today, stands here.
1.  Only 35 tests done per million in India as compared to 8000+ in Germany, Italy, South Korea.
2.  Only 0.55 Bed per 1000 People. That means 1000 people will have to share that half bed, right? That‚Äôs scary! And we proclaim ‚ÄòMake in India‚Äô?
3.  Only 112 operational test centers for 1.3 Billion Population? 
4.  Millions are Stranded, homeless and are dying of poverty!  They are struggling to find food, forget about burning candles. They don‚Äôt have the luxury to switch on the Torches or Mobile Flashlights because they don‚Äôt own one!
5. The Administration and Police are confused and clearly not helping much; commonsense, they are led by uneducated Politicians like you all. Of course, we are to be blamed.
6. National Media is not making sense at all. Calling them 'shit' is more apt. That ‚ÄòFaggot‚Äô Arnab is literally burning the country with his communal propaganda. We can discuss that later.
7. The PPE Units meant for Govt. hospitals will take another 25 days to be delivered. India's target was for 10 lakh protective suits. Even at the optimistic estimate of producing 8,000 PPE suits per day, it would take four months to produce 10 lakh of them. (Courtesy TOI)
Perhaps more worrying is the question of whether even the 10 lakh PPE suits will be sufficient.
8. Our Forefront warriors are crying out to you for help. And here you came up with this ‚ÄòMahaan‚Äô 9 minutes Theory?
Yes, this morning, after your ‚ÄòGyan‚Äô Video Message to the Country, you had a video conference call with the Country‚Äôs Sportspersons? Seriously? Your intervention was needed to boost their Morale? What about the ones fighting to save the Country? Well, we all heard your Phone call to that sister Nurse in the South some days back. Even my 3-year-old boy could make sense of your tone and halfhearted gimmick phone call!
10. And let us not forget those who are under severe Health Conditions, Dialysis, Stroke, Cancer, Organ transplant, to name a few.
How are we accommodating them? Definitely not by Clapping our Hands or Lighting that Candle? Hello!

For once let's be logical. Singing, Clapping, Candle Burning- Italy did all that before you. Don‚Äôt be a copy. Mind you, Italy isn‚Äôt doing very well right now. What we need now is a real man with a real solution. Not clapping Hands or Switching on the Torch or Burning the Candle. We can all do that together once we conquer this Fight and emerge victoriously and lessons learned.

Did you forget, it was Taali, Thali and Bartaans for 5 minutes which turned into mad celebrations, all over the country? This time around the Candle burning and Mobile Flashlights won't be any different from what history taught us.

Why are you so arrogant and foolish? We wanted to hear the following:
1. What is the Government doing to contain the virus?
2. What is the plan of action to protect our medical practitioners?
3.  How will the testing kits reach every district of the country? Nagaland is a state where there is no test facility. Even the Government Helpline Numbers aren't attended. It's a joke.
4. How do you plan to provide food and supplies to the poor and migrant laborers and the jobless? We small businesses Entrepreneurs are still paying our employees, by the way!
5. Most importantly, what is your plan of action on the 22nd Day? Because I see more ‚ÄòTaalis‚Äô, ‚ÄòThalis‚Äô, ‚ÄòCandle Burning‚Äô on the streets as if the war is won!

This time don‚Äôt let that Sadhu/Astrologer/Numerologist run the country.
You ‚ÄòBe a Man. Grab those Balls and Do the Right Thing‚Äô.

You know what my Family will do on 5th April 2020 at 9 PM?
I will let you know soon.

Regards
Khroku Nuh
Dimapur, Nagaland

*Cannot be any better joke than this at this time!*

*Right in Time Joke.* 

*An American, a German and a Chinese.. got arrested consuming alcohol which is a severe offense in Saudi Arabia.*
 
*So for the terrible crime, they are all sentenced 20 lashes each of the whip.*

*As they were preparing for their punishment, the Sheik announced:*

*‚ÄúIt‚Äôs my first wife‚Äôs birthday today, and she has asked me to allow each of you one wish before your whipping..‚Äù*

*The German was first in line, he thought for a while and then said: ‚ÄúPlease tie a pillow to my back..‚Äù*

*This was done, but the pillow only lasted 10 lashes & the German had to be carried away bleeding and crying with pain.*

*The Chinese was next up. After watching the German in horror he said smugly: ‚ÄúPlease fix two pillows to my back.‚Äù*

*But even two pillows could only take 15 lashes & the Chinese was also led away whimpering loudly.*

*The American was the last one up, but before he could say anything, the Sheikh turned to him and said:*
*‚ÄúI like you Americans. . For this, you may have two wishes!‚Äù*

*‚ÄúThank you, your Most Royal and Merciful highness,‚Äù American replied.*

*‚ÄúIn recognition of your kindness, my first wish is that you give me not 20, but 100 lashes.‚Äù*

*‚ÄúNot only are you an honourable, handsome and powerful man, you are also very brave.‚Äù The Sheik said with an admiring look on his face.*

*‚ÄúIf 100 lashes is what you desire, then so be it.*

*‚ÄúAnd what is your second wish, ?‚Äù the Sheik asked.*

*American  smiled and said, ‚ÄúTie the Chinese to my back‚Äù !!!*

Govt didn't incentivized or build confidence among masses to come forward and get themselves tested rather than demonizing them (E.g.Tablighi Jamaat whose intemperate vilification was done by the lapdogs of the govt.)

The data collected of different districts/zones was largely incorrect.
E.g. Multiple entries of an  individual counted as different person, no test in some areas considered as no cases..etc., so zonal classification was erroneous.

Govt. didn't ensured door-to-door testing/surveillance in highly concentrated residential areas ( more prone to virus due to public toilets, close proximity..etc) of urban pockets as the corona carriers were first spotted in the urban.
E.g. Dharavi, Mumbai which has 800 active cases, 35 fatalities

Policy paralysis, irregularities in the functioning, abrupt changes in the benchmarks.

No effective social welfare schemes for the people at the bottom of pyramid resulting in  humanitarian crisis.

Experts are predicting 2 lakh cases by 31st May and 22 Lakhs cases and 72000 deaths by 30th June.

6/4/20, 12:34 - Nadeem Bhai: An Important thread on Pandit Exodus.

During the armed rebellion of 1989, many Kashmiris who were believed to be supporting Indian rule in Kashmir were selectively killed. Several Kashmiri Pandits were also killed, mostly on allegations of being informers of the government.

The first militant attack was on a Muslim police officer, Ali Muhammad Watali. The first militancy related civilian killing was also of a Muslim, Muhammad Yusuf Halwai, on 21 August 1989. He was an activist of National Conference.

Mir Mustafa, a former legislator, was kidnapped and killed on 21 March 1990. Professor Mushir-ul-Haq, VC of the University of Kashmir and Abdul Gani were kidnapped and killed on 6 April 1990. On 23 December 1990, senior politician Maulana Mohammad Sayeed Masoodi was gunned down.

Some Kashmiri Pandits like Tika Lal Tapiloo of BJP, Neel Kant Ganjoo - a sessions judge who ordered the hanging of Maqbool Bhat, Lassa Koul ‚Äì Director of Doordarshan Srinagar and Pushkar Nath ‚Äì Assistant Director in the State Information Department ‚Äî were also killed.

All these killings were political rather than communal in nature. The first militancy related abduction was also of a Muslim Kashmiri woman, Rubaiya Sayeed, who was later released in exchange of five jailed rebels.

As per Anuradha Bhasin, "Many of them (Kashmiri Pandits) were shot dead for their affiliation with the intelligence agencies or their role in the government decision- making. Kashmiri Pandits occupied a prominent place in government jobs and bureaucracy."

Recently, AS Dulat was the IB chief in Kashmir during the 90s also accepted that IB, in J&K, had a fair amount of Kashmiri Pandits. ‚ÄúThey sneaked in and out of all sorts of places and got the intelligence flowing‚Ä¶ they rendered yeoman service to the nation."

On 1 March 1990, Almost a million Kashmiris marched towards the Headquarters of UNMOGIP to handover a memorandum seeking freedom of Kashmir from the Indian rule. The demonstration continued for days without a break but not a single Pandit or his/her property was harmed.

"Our community should not forget that those thousands who came out on the street did not attack or vandalize even a single Pandit home." Vijay Bakaya [Prominent Kashmiri Pandit and Former Chief Secretary J&K]

Rastriya Seva Dal, after visiting Jammu & Kashmir in April 1990, wrote in a report published by the Economic and Political Weekly that-

"The exodus of Hindu refugees... is due to the tremendous fear created by the large rallies and angry demonstrations against the Government by the majority community. The Muslims claim amd the refugees agree that there were no communal incidents or burning or looting of houses, misbehaviour with women etc. The refugees say that they left their houses because they feared that something of this kind would happen in future."

"Whether the Islamic sloganeering from mosques was widespread or this happened only in selected pockets, since there is no recorded document or media reports, the truth is likely to be a causality with imagination and prejudice clouding the real picture." 

"Whether the Islamic sloganeering from mosques was widespread or this happened only in selected pockets, since there is no recorded document or media reports, the truth is likely to be a casuality with imagination and prejudice clouding the real picture. But the moot question is: would the response be so uniform in the event of one or even all mosques of the valley echoing the Islamic slogans? Was there some underlying unheard, unsaid, understood threat that motivated the Pandits to migrate in masses within two days. Why in just two days the entire scenario changed? Why did the 'Islamic' militarization suddenly become threatening since the killings were going on for months. The media obviously has done no homework."~Anuradha Bhasin [Auditing the Mainstream Media: The Case of Jammu and Kashmir]

Most of the Kashmiri Pandits were unaware of the Government's plan to shift them to Jammu or other places temporarily to pave a way for a massive crackdown on the Muslims. Here is how Kashmiri Muslims helped their brethren.

"In the late 1989, when militancy surfaced in the valley, the Muslims in general, whether as a neighbour, friend, or a colleague asked their Pandit brothers not to leave homes and provided security for them. Many Muslims accommodated Pandit families in their homes to save them from militant attacks. There are instances when Muslim ladies, at the risk of their lives, stood at the door of Pandit houses, to stop militants from entering their houses. When in danger, they would also provide timely information to the Pandits so that they can flee to safety." ~O. N. Trissal [Kashmiri Pandit : At the Crossroads of History]

In April 1990, Justice V. M. Tarkunde visited Kashmir and reported total communal harmony, - 
"Hindus have received full cooperation from the local Muslims. The Muslims shared their relations amd other items of the day to day requirements with them. There os total communal harmony in Kashmir. Those people who had come out had either overreacted to the situation or had done so because of other reasons which could be winter, curfew, or closure of offices amd educational institutions. Not a single case of looting or arson of non-Muslim property had taken place".
~ Justice V. M. Tarkunde [Report on Kashmir, April 1990]

All these statements prove that there were no blood-thirsty frenzied mobs on streets or in mosques who forced the Kashmiri Pandits to migrate. How would it have been possible? Kashmir was under curfew and shoot at sight orders were implemented on 17 January itself.

"There is no dispute about the fact that Kashmiri Pandit community was made a scapegoat by Jagmohan, some self-styled leaders of our community and other vested interests‚Ä¶. The plan was to make Kashmiri Pandits migrate from the valley so that the mass uprising against occupational forces could be painted as a communal flare up... Some self-styled leaders begged the Pandits to migrate from the valley. We were told that our migration was very vital for preserving amd protecting our 'Dharam' and the unity of India. We were told our migration would pave the way for realizing the dream of 'Akhand Bharat... We were fooled and we were more than wiling to become fools. "
~ A Kashmiri Pandit to Human Rights Watch [Report : Kashmir Under Siege]

"Pandits were assured by the government that once the proposed massacre of Muslims in Kashmir was completed and the movement curbed, they would be sent back to the valley. My community now understands that it was a very crude way of painting the mass uprising against India as nothing but a communal flare up. The Indian government tried to fool the world by depicting the uprising as a handiwork of Muslim Fundamentalists who had turned against non-Muslims and had thrown them out of their homes. I know my community has lost the affection, love, respect and goodwill of Kashmiri Muslims for having betrayed them. I feel ashamed to admit that my community has stabbed the Muslims in the back. This all happened at the instance of Jagmohan. Some self-styled Pandit leaders exploited the situation and Pandits became refugees in their own land."
~ A Kashmiri Pandit, K. L. Koul in the Daily Alsafa [18/9/1990]

In this letter below, Rajnath Turki, a Kashmiri Pandit writes to his friend Mushtaq Wani about how the security forces at Karan Nagar forced him to leave.

Dear Mushtaq,
20/12/1990
        Hope by God's grace everybody is fine there. I tried to write you earlier but due to ill health had to postpone it. Anyhow how is everybody there. I came here in the end July. That too when security people at Karan Nagar forced us to leave...

In a letter published in the Daily Alsafa on 18 September 1990, K.L. Koul also wrote - "In the first week of February , a word was sent to the members of the Pandit community in Kashmir and they were asked to migrate to safer places. This message from Jagmohan was conveyed through some self-styled Pandit leaders. Pandits were told that the government had plans of killing about one lakh Muslim, particularly the youth, in order to crush the uprising. Pandits were assured that they would be looked after well, that they would be provided with free ration, free releif, jobs, and free accommodation. Pandits were assured that once the Muslims were massacred they would be sent back. This is how Pandits left."

Kashmiri Pandits faced overwhelming problems in Jammu and continue to do so. The weather was hot, tents were crowded, washrooms were ill-equipped. Young Pandit girls were subjected to stalking on daily basis. Kashmiri Pandits were facing an identity and cultural crisis.

"We were not welcomed by Hindu Dogras, our co-religionists in Jammu who felt that we will compete with them for jobs and business on the one hand, and on the other hand we never felt close to them culturally as we used to feel for Kashmiri Muslims... The respect which Kashmiri Muslims used to give us was a distant dream in Jammu"~A migrant Kashmiri Pandit in Jammu, Bhan to Human Rights Watch.

As per some Indian Media channels and Kashmiri Pandit organizations, 3,50,000 to 7,00,000 Kashmiri Pandits were forced to migrate from Jammu &amp; Kashmir but according to the Census of 1981 the total population of Hindus (including non- Kashmiris) was 124,078.

Given the decade growth of the community from 1971 to 1981 as 6.75% their population in 1991 would have been around 132,000. If we subtract at least 8,000 Kashmiri Pandits who didn‚Äôt leave the valley, we get almost 124,000 Kashmiri Pandits who migrated.

Following the migration, BJP came up with a list of 55 allegedly destroyed temples in Kashmir. On the day of the demolition of Babri Masjid (6 December 1992), Lal Krishna Advani claimed 55 temples had been destroyed in #Kashmir. He lied.

"Following the Pandit migration, BJP came up with a list of 55 allegedly destroyed temples in Kashmir. On the day of demolition of Babri Masjid (6 December 1992), Lal Krishna Advani said : "Everybody wants to defend Babri Masjid, none of them have spoken a word of criticism about the 55 temples destroyed in Kashmir." After being questioned over it, he reduced the number to 40 in another rally. Journalist Harinder Baweja busted this myth with photographic evidence and revealed that the BJP had misled people to score political points. Harinder Baweja visited 23 temples from the list provided by the BJP and found all of them safe and functioning. These temples, according to BJP, according to BJP, had been burnt and demolished. 

One pujari of Ganpatyar Temple, which the BJP claimed had been destroyed said that Puja had continued in the 200-year-old Hanuman temple.

In another instance, a Kashmiri Pandit, Maheshwar Nath told Baweja: " Gita ki kasam, this temple has never been touched." When Advani was confronted on this issue and accused of lying and distorting facts, he denied any such list existed.

Journalist Harinder Baweja had busted this myth with photographic evidence and revealed that the BJP had misled people to score political points. In many cases, Muslims have been taking care of temples since decades.

Many non-Kashmiri Pujaris came from India and took over the temples here. These Pujaris started selling away various properties that the temples owned. In one case three Pujaris looked over 375 Kanals of temple land which they had rented to non-state-subjects, violating the Article 370.

In another case, a lease holder, Kuldeep Narayan Jaggi sold the rented land illegally for 2.5 Crore. Even an ancient idol from the temple is missing. Some Kashmiri Pandits say assets worth Rs 500 Crore are already sold out.

Source - Kashmir: Exposing the Myth behind the Narrative By Khalid Bashir Ahmad.

Via Rayees Chowdhary

8/14/20, 09:11 - Nadeem Bhai: On this Day in 1980 : Moradabad Eidgah Firing

On 13 August, 1980 as Muslims were celebrating Eid throughout India, the police and Provincial Armed Constabulary opened fire on the Moradabad Eidgah where around 40,000 Muslims had gathered to offer prayers. Around 300 Muslims were killed.

Compare that to Jallianwala Bagh, where thousands had gathered on the day of Baisakhi to celebrate and protest. The army under the command of Dyer opened fire, killing around 400 people. The similarities do not end there. In both cases, the victims were fired upon and confined to closed spaces with only one exit point which was blocked. Then MP Syed Shahabuddin called the Moradabad firing the Jallianwala Bagh of independent India. And rightly so.

BJP leader and Former External affairs minister MJ Akbar, who was a young journalist at that time, reported from Moradabad. He wrote in his book Riot after Riot:  ‚ÄúMen of the Provincial Armed Constabulary opened fire on about 40,000 Muslims while they were at Eid prayers. No one knows exactly how many people died. What is known is that the incident at Moradabad was not a Hindu-Muslim riot but a calculated cold-blooded massacre of Muslims by a rabidly communal police force which tried to cover up its genocide by making it out to be a Hindu-Muslim riot.‚Äù

9/4/20, 12:29 - Nadeem Bhai: <Media omitted>
9/4/20, 12:30 - Nadeem Bhai: Here is a curious case of "Missing 11 days" . 3rd September in 1752 is an incredibly remarkable day in Britain‚Äôs history, simply because it had never existed. Not only that, from 3rd September to 13th September, 11 long days were also absolutely wiped out from the history of Britain. Millions of Brits went to bed on September 2, 1752, and woke up the next day morning straight on September 14. The reason? This was the day Britain decided to make a switch to Gregorian calendar from Julian calendar which already had been obsolete for the rest of the world & to sync up perfectly they had to skip 11 days in future. These days simply never existed ‚Äì no births, no marriages, no deaths, no recorded events. There were possible riots that happened in villages as protest, & due to growing agitation, the Government eventually decided that all workers would be given salaries for these missing 11 days. This was also the birth of the concept of ‚Äòpaid leave‚Äô, which is being followed even today.

10/4/20, 22:41 - Nadeem Bhai: Beautiful names of our Rabb 

Allah - The Most commonly used name for One and Only God, The Creator, Cherisher and Sustainer of all. 

"Indeed, I am Allah. There is no God except Me, so worship Me and establish prayer for My remembrance."
(Holy Quran 20:14) 

"The most beautiful names belong to Allah: Invoke Him by them." 
(Holy Quran 7:180)

To worship Allah and remember Him, it is important to know His beautiful names and attributes. 

Let's do Bismillah - In the name of Allah. 

Let's try to learn those beautiful names, so that we can beseech Him through them, cherishing the amazing faith which we will gain by knowing Allah through His beautiful attributes.

Abu Huraira (r.a) reported: The Messenger of Allah (peace and blessings be upon him), said, ‚ÄúAllah has ninety-nine names and whoever preserves them will enter Paradise.‚Äù
Muttafaqun Alayhi (agreed upon). 

Before starting to learn to glorify the beautiful attributes of Allah, let's address one prevailing and confusing question about the name - Allah.

The question is -
"Why Allah is addressed as He and not she or it?" 

This issue comes into the scene when we don't know the rules of Arabic language. 
In Arabic language everything is either addressed in a masculine gender or in a feminine gender and there is no "it" for gender neutral entities, so everything is addressed in masculine gender even if it is not meant so, like Qalam (pen) is Qalamun and it is masculine gender, had it been a feminine gender, there would have been an addition of ta marbuta.
Although, we know Qalam (pen) is addressed as masculine gender but in reality it is not a masculine entity. 
Arabic is different from English to have a neutral gender rule and even in French everything addressed is either masculine or feminine and things by default are addressed as masculine and for it to be feminine, an additional alphabet is bound to be added. 
So, linguistically we understand that Allah is neither male nor female and is above of such genders, Allah is addressed as He because of linguistics. 

Allah is Unique and is not like any of His creation as is mentioned by Him in Surah Ikhlas, chapter 112.

To read more articles like this, please download this app https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.oliventech.alasmaulhusna

10/22/20, 09:59 - +91 96250 85822: A Russian Jew had been allowed to emigrate to Israel. 

At Moscow airport, customs found a Lenin statue in his baggage and asked him, "What is this?"

The man replied, "What is this? Wrong question comrade. You should have asked : Who is he? This is Comrade Lenin. He laid the foundations of socialism and created the future and prosperity of the Russian people. I am taking it with me as a memory of our hero days."

The Russian customs officer was a bit shamed and let him go without further inspection.

At Tel Aviv airport, the customs officer also asks our friend, "What is this?"

He replies, "What is this? Wrong question Sir. You should be asking 'Who is this?' This is Lenin, a bastard that made me, as a Jew leave Russia. I take this statue with me so I can curse him every day."

The Israeli customs officer said, "I apologize Sir, you can go on."

In Israel, when he arrives at his new house, he puts the statue on a table. 

To celebrate his immigration, he invite his friends and relatives to dinner. 

One of his friends asks him, "Who is this?"

He replies, "My dear friend, 'Who is this' is a wrong question. You should have asked, What is this? This is ten kilograms of solid gold that I managed to bring with me without customs and tax."

3/26/22, 11:52 - Nadeem Bhai: *Shaheen Academy Lucknow*
_*Entrance and Scholarship Exam (SSGL) - 2022*_

_*Shaheen Scholarship Group Lucknow (SSGL) Exam ‚Äì 2022*_ is a social initiative by *Shaheen Academy Lucknow* in collaboration with *Association of Muslims Professionals* to select *500 deserving meritorious students* throughout India, especially from UP/Bihar/Jharkhand and provide intensive coaching with residential facilities and guide them towards achieving excellence in different professional education like _NEET/IIT-JEE/UPSC/PCS-J_.

*Important Dates:* 
o _*Exam Date:*_  Sunday, 3rd April 2022
o _*Last date of Registration:*_ Thursday, 31st March 2022 at 12 midnight

*Venue:* Online
*Registration/Participation Fee:* It's FREE

*Register Here:* https://bit.ly/Shaheen_SSCL_22

*Exam Duration:*
For NEET - 2 hours ( 10:00 AM - 12:00 PM).
For XI - 90 minutes ( 1:30 PM - 3:00 PM).
For IX - 90 minutes ( 4:00 PM - 5:30 PM).

*How scholarships are given?*
_The 500 students selected through SSG - 2022 would be categorized into 4 groups for the awarding of Scholarships._
*Rankers* - Selected students would be given 100% tuition fee concession (max 10 students) worth 6 lacs.
*Achievers* - This group of students would be given 75% tuition fee concession (max 10 students) worth 4.5 lacs.
*Winners* - Students in this group would be given 50% tuition fee concession (max 20 students) worth 3 lacs.
*Racers* - Students in this group would be given 25% tuition fee concession (max 30 students) worth 4.5 lacs.

_*Courses*_
1. *Class 9th - 10th Integrated with NEET/JEE:*
Two-year classroom course is the quintessential program for students who wish to start early in their quest to excel NEE/IIT-JEE/UPSC/PCS-J.
*Who can apply:*
Students appearing in Class VIII exam in the year-2022 or VIII passed.

2. *Class XI-XII:*
Science Integrated with NEET/IIT-JEE/UPSC/PCS-J
*Who can apply:*
Students appearing in Class - X exam in the year 2022.

3. *NEET Repeater:*
1-year course to prepare for NEET exam.
*Who can apply:*
Students appearing in Class -XII exam in the year 2022.

*Questions and Marking Details:*
1. NEET: Total Questions - 90, +4 for every correct answer (No negative marking).
2. XI: Total Questions - 60, +4 for every correct answer (No negative marking).
3. IX: Total Questions - 40, +4 for every correct answer (No negative marking).

*Find more information at:* shaheengroup.org

*Note:* Students registered with Indian Schools & Colleges only can participate.

Regards,
Team Shaheen Academy Lucknow & AMP
